            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FPGAM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Prompt gammas were detected at 55 degree."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A single target was irradiated with deuteron",
                "beam in the energy range 1400 - 1500 keV.",
                "Gamma-rays, protons and backscattered deuterons were",
                "detected simultaneously. The energy loss in the Pd",
                "layer (4.4 keV) was calculated with the SRIM code.",
                "The number of target nuclei was determined with RBS",
                "technique using alpha beam of 1.5 MeV energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A thin film of NaCl (thickness: 8.4*10e17 atom/cm2)",
                "evaporated on a self-supported thin film of Ag was",
                "used for the measurement of the excitation function of",
                "the 23Na(p,p0g)23Na reaction in the 1900-1959 keV",
                "energy range. Since the parameters of the included",
                "1931 keV resonance have well established values in",
                "the literature, the reliability of the experimental",
                "arrangement, fitting and evaluating process could be",
                "checked by comparing the measured and reported data."
              ]
            }
          ],
